OL,3,CCalls for resignation over 'very short
OL,4,Cskirts' remark
OL,6,F"If John Dwyer was sincere about
OL,7,Ftackling violence against women and
OL,8,Fgirls he would have already resigned.
OL,9,FHis outdated and offensive views make
OL,10,Fit impossible for him to continue."
OL,12,FThe comments by Mr Dwyer have also
OL,13,Fbeen called "sexist, misogynistic, and
OL,14,Foutdated" by Labour's MP for Weaver
OL,15,FVale Mike Amesbury.
OL,17,FCalling for him to resign Mr Amesbury
OL,18,Fsaid it was now impossible for him to
OL,19,Fbe "taken seriously".
